<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="537" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="537">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="537">
Carapace pyriform, covered with short setae. Pseudorostral spine short, diverging. Supraorbital eave with sharp preorbital spine; postorbital lobe fused to hepatic plate on large size specimens. Carapace with plates: 1 hepatic plate pointing upwards, 1 short mesogastric spine above 1 oblong mesogastric plate, 1 large protogastric granule, 1 oblong cardiac plate, 1 large epibranchial plate, 1 mesobranchial plate, 1 posterior blunt spine, 1 lateral branchial plate curved upwards (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Scyramathia hertwigi Doflein, in Chun 1900, lectotype male (33.7 x 27.0 mm) (ZMB 13699), South Atlantic Ocean. A. overall dorsal view; B. overall ventral view; C. lateral view of carapace." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.48041.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447927" pageId="0" pageNumber="537">10A</figureCitation>
). Plates less distinct on juvenile specimens. Antennal flagellum equal to or slightly longer than pseudorostral spines. Basal antennal article with convex outer margin, with blunt distal angle of article. Buccal frame covered by third maxilliped, distal angle of buccal frame raised, distinct. Pterygostomial region plate-like with 3 or 4 granules on outer margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Scyramathia hertwigi Doflein, in Chun 1900, lectotype male (33.7 x 27.0 mm) (ZMB 13699), South Atlantic Ocean. A. overall dorsal view; B. overall ventral view; C. lateral view of carapace." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.48041.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447927" pageId="0" pageNumber="537">10B</figureCitation>
). Chelipeds slender, propodus longer than fingers, slightly carinate; carpus with granules on carina margin; merus triangular in cross-section, granulated on edge. Ambulatory legs slender; merus cylindrical; male P2 merus length 0.8-1.2 times carapace length, female P2 merus length 0.4-0.8 times carapace length, male P2 merus length 10.9-14.9 times width, female P2 merus length about 8.5 times width; male P5 merus length 0.4-0.6 times carapace length, female P5 merus length 0.4-0.5 times carapace length, male P5 merus length 4-6.8 times width, female P5 merus length 4.6-5.8 times width (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Scyramathia hertwigi Doflein, in Chun 1900, lectotype male (33.7 x 27.0 mm) (ZMB 13699), South Atlantic Ocean. A. overall dorsal view; B. overall ventral view; C. lateral view of carapace." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.48041.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447927" pageId="0" pageNumber="537">10A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Dorsal view of P 5. A, B. Scyramathia carpenteri (Norman, in Thomson 1873); A. male (41.3 x 34.0 mm) (NHM 1983.449), North Sea; B. ovigerous female (35.8 x 29.0 mm) (NHM 1978.99), Atlantic Ocean; C, D. S. hertwigi Doflein, in Chun 1900; C. male (34.6 x 27.3 mm) (NHM 1924.7.19.1 - 3), South Africa; D. female (24.5 x 18.4 mm) (SAM-A 47872), South Africa; E, S. umbonata (Stimpson, 1871), female (36.7 x 27.9 mm) (NSMT-Cr 7178), off Suriname; F-J. S. tenuipes sp. nov.; F. holotype male (33.9 x 26.3 mm) (ICMD 288), Mediterranean Sea; G. paratype male (29.7 x 22.0 mm) (ICMD 000707), Mediterranean Sea; H. paratype male (32.0 x 25.4 mm) (ZRC 2019.1636), Mediterranean Sea,; I. paratype ovigerous female (31.2 x 24.6 mm) (ICMD 000708), Mediterranean Sea,; J. paratype ovigerous female (32.2 x 25.8 mm) (ZRC 2019.1635), Mediterranean Sea." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.48041.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447931" pageId="0" pageNumber="537">14C, D</figureCitation>
). Male thoracic sternum wide, concave on sternites 1-4; regions well defined; sternites 3, 4 widest, lateral margins slightly constricted medially. Male pleon with triangular telson; surface of somites smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Scyramathia hertwigi Doflein, in Chun 1900, lectotype male (33.7 x 27.0 mm) (ZMB 13699), South Atlantic Ocean. A. overall dorsal view; B. overall ventral view; C. lateral view of carapace." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.48041.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447927" pageId="0" pageNumber="537">10B</figureCitation>
). G1 straight with flattened sharp tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. A-D. Scyramathia hertwigi Doflein, in Chun 1900, paralectotype male (24.7 x 19.0 mm) (ZMB 13700), Agulhasstrom [= Agulhas current], left G 1; E-H. Scyramathia tenuipes sp. nov., holotype male (33.9 x 26.3 mm) (ICMD 288), Mediterranean Sea, left G 1. A, E. ventral view; B, F. ventral view of distal portion; C, G. dorsal view; D, H. dorsal view of distal portion. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.48041.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447932" pageId="0" pageNumber="537">15A-D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
